    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 486.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Lewis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 12, 1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No. 11,
                    and to express satisfaction with the tenor of the note from the foreign office,
                    a copy of which you inclose, promising measures of redress in the case of the
                    missionaries, American citizens, lately expelled from Bihé and Bailunda, West
                    Africa. It is hoped that their property will be recovered and that their future
                    immunity from molestation is secured.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAS. D. PORTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
